tic world of the second and first millennia BCE to the temple cult at the time of Jesus. He tells the stories of the rabbis, mystics, and messiahs of the medieval and early modern periods and guides us through the many varieties of Judaism today. Goodman's compelling narrative spans the globe, from the Middle East, Europe, and America to North Africa, China, and India. He explains the institutions and ideas on which all forms of Judaism are based, and masterfully weaves together the different threads of doctrinal and philosophical debate that run throughout its history.A History of Judaism is a spellbinding chronicle of a vibrant and multifaceted religious tradition that has shaped the spiritual heritage of humankind like no other.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Sep 2021) 0aJudaismxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060659140uhttps://doi.org/10.23943/9781400890019zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400890019423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781400890019/original  a978-3-11-060659-1  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles